President Biden has declared a state of emergency in Oklahoma due to a severe winter storm that began on February 8, 2021. This declaration allows the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to coordinate relief efforts and provide assistance to the affected areas. FEMA is authorized to mobilize resources and equipment to alleviate the impacts of the emergency. Emergency protective measures and direct federal assistance will be provided with 75 percent federal funding. Adam D. Burpee has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.